snippet.textDisplay: can i go now? i asked myself, can i go now? i kept asking. i want to go home, only to realise the home i once knew no longer exists. and so i wait, and wait, for a bus to take me home, knowing full well no such bus will ever arrive at this stop. perhaps its time to let the rain cry for me, and walk on my own two feet towards home, my home. i know i will walk pass this rain, and i know you can too. we are on different paths but we are all walking at the same time.
